{"ts": "2026-04-04T14:51:51.425", "event": "PostToolUse:raw_input", "raw_input": {"session_id": "40302fac-b037-4b24-b2d0-deb954ba8d45", "transcript_path": "/home/emhar/.claude/projects/-home-emhar-avaris-ai/40302fac-b037-4b24-b2d0-deb954ba8d45.jsonl", "cwd": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai", "permission_mode": "plan", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Agent", "tool_input": {"description": "Find all state.json consumers", "prompt": "In /home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/, find ALL files that:\n1. Import or use `SessionState` or `StateStore`\n2. Reference `state.json` directly (path strings)\n3. Reference `DEFAULT_STATE_PATH`\n\nFor each file found, note:\n- The file path\n- How it uses state (reads, writes, resets, etc.)\n- Whether it uses session_id or defaults to the single state.json\n\nAlso read the FileManager class at /home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/lib/file_manager.py to understand how file locking works.\n\nBe thorough - check all subdirectories including guards/, dispatchers/, utils/, config/, templates/, headless_claude/, tests/.", "subagent_type": "Explore"}, "tool_response": {"status": "completed", "prompt": "In /home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/, find ALL files that:\n1. Import or use `SessionState` or `StateStore`\n2. Reference `state.json` directly (path strings)\n3. Reference `DEFAULT_STATE_PATH`\n\nFor each file found, note:\n- The file path\n- How it uses state (reads, writes, resets, etc.)\n- Whether it uses session_id or defaults to the single state.json\n\nAlso read the FileManager class at /home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/lib/file_manager.py to understand how file locking works.\n\nBe thorough - check all subdirectories including guards/, dispatchers/, utils/, config/, templates/, headless_claude/, tests/.", "agentId": "a99f8d29fcc6aa7f6", "agentType": "Explore", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Perfect! I have completed a thorough search of the workflow directory. Let me now provide you with a comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive State Management Analysis Report\n\n### **FileManager Class (File Locking Implementation)**\n**Location:** `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/lib/file_manager.py`\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Uses `filelock.FileLock` for atomic read-modify-write operations on JSON files\n- Wraps all file operations with locks when `lock=True` (default)\n- Lock file created at `{state_path}.lock`\n- Methods: `load_file()`, `save_file()`, `update_file(callback)`, `delete_file()`\n- `update_file()` implements callback pattern for safe mutations\n\n---\n\n### **State Architecture**\n\n#### **StateStore Class** (Base State Wrapper)\n**Location:** `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/state_store.py`\n\n- **Single flat-file state model** at arbitrary `Path` with optional `default_state`\n- **Methods:**\n  - `load()` - reads JSON, returns empty dict if not exists\n  - `save(state)` - writes entire state file\n  - `update(fn)` - atomic read-modify-write with callback\n  - `get(key, default)` - reads single key\n  - `set(key, value)` - writes single key atomically\n  - `reset(default_state)` - clears to empty/default\n  - `reinitialize(initial_state)` - replaces entire state\n  - `delete()` - removes state file\n  - `archive(history_path)` - appends current state as JSONL entry\n- **File Locking:** Uses FileManager internally with locks enabled by default\n\n#### **SessionState Class** (Session-Scoped Wrapper)\n**Location:** `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/session_state.py`\n\n- Extends `StateStore`\n- **Two Path Modes:**\n  1. **No session_id** \u2192 Uses `DEFAULT_STATE_PATH = ./state.json` (single global state)\n  2. **With session_id** \u2192 Uses `.claude/sessions/session_{session_id}/state.json` (per-session)\n- **Properties:** workflow_type, workflow_active, session_id, story_id, TDD, tool_enforcement, force_stop, phases, plan_mode, pr, ci, files\n- **Typed Setters:** set_workflow_active(), set_session_id(), set_story_id(), etc.\n- **Helper Methods:** find_file(), get_files(), add_file()\n- **Initialization:** initialize(), get_default_state(), default_pr_review_session()\n\n---\n\n### **Files Using SessionState or StateStore**\n\n#### **1. Core State Initialization**\n\n| File Path | Usage Type | Session ID Mode | Details |\n|-----------|-----------|-----------------|---------|\n| `/lib/set_story_id.py` | SessionState(session_id) | **Per-session** | Initializes session with story_id, session_id, workflow_active=True |\n| `/lib/workflow_initializer.py` | StateStore(DEFAULT_STATE_PATH) | **Global** | Placeholder for workflow setup |\n\n#### **2. Dispatchers (Entry Points for Hook Events)**\n\n| File | Event | State Usage | Session Mode | Details |\n|------|-------|------------|--------------|---------|\n| `/dispatchers/session_start.py` | SessionStart:clear | StateStore(DEFAULT_STATE_PATH) | **Global** | Checks workflow_active, phase, advances after plan approval |\n| `/dispatchers/pre_tool_use.py` | PreToolUse | StateStore(DEFAULT_STATE_PATH) | **Global** | Routes to guardrail.py & recorder.py; reads state for reminders |\n| `/dispatchers/post_tool_use.py` | PostToolUse | StateStore(DEFAULT_STATE_PATH) | **Global** | Tracks phase transitions, injects reminders |\n| `/dispatchers/subagent_start.py` | SubagentStart | StateStore(DEFAULT_STATE_PATH) | **Global** | Reads state, injects agent-role reminders |\n| `/dispatchers/subagent_stop.py` | SubagentStop | StateStore(DEFAULT_STATE_PATH) | **Global** | Calls guardrail & recorder; logs phase transitions |\n| `/dispatchers/user_prompt_submit.py` | UserPromptSubmit | StateStore(DEFAULT_STATE_PATH) | **Global** | Checks workflow_active & phase for explore kickoff |\n\n#### **3. Core Guards (Validation Logic)**\n\n| File | State Usage | Session Mode | Key Features |\n|------|------------|--------------|--------------|\n| `/guards/write_guard.py` | StateStore.load() | **Global** | Validates Write/Edit phases; reads phase, workflow_active |\n| `/guards/bash_guard.py` | StateStore.load() | **Global** | Validates git commit format & PR commands; reads phase |\n| `/guards/stop_guard.py` | StateStore.load() | **Global** | Blocks stop unless workflow complete; reads phase, validation_result, ci_check_executed, pr_status |\n| `/guards/read_guard.py` | StateStore.load() | **Global** | Enforces plan-scoped file reads; reads plan_file, plan_files_cache, files_written |\n| `/guards/agent_guard.py` | StateStore.load() | **Global** | Validates agent launches per phase; reads agents list, skip_explore, skip_research |\n| `/guards/task_guard.py` | StateStore.update() | **Global** | Caches project tasks; reads/writes story_id, tasks, subtasks |\n| `/guards/skill_guard.py` | StateStore.reinitialize() | **Global** | Activates /plan or /implement workflows |\n| `/guards/webfetch_guard.py` | StateStore.load() | **Global** | Validates WebFetch during coding phases |\n| `/guards/subagent_stop_guard.py` | StateStore.load() | **Global** | Validates agent output before recorder processes it |\n\n#### **4. Core Recorder (State Mutation Logic)**\n\n**Location:** `/recorder.py`\n\n**Environment Variable:** `RECORDER_STATE_PATH` (overrides DEFAULT_STATE_PATH)\n\n**Mutations by Event:**\n- **PreToolUse(Agent):** Records agent entry as \"running\"; may advance phase write-code\u2192validate\n- **PostToolUse(Write/Edit):** Tracks written files; advances phases on plan/test/CODEBASE.md writes; handles CI regression\n- **PostToolUse(Bash):** Tracks test runs, PR creation, CI checks; parses CI output to determine status\n- **PostToolUse(ExitPlanMode):** Advances phase based on workflow type (task-create/write-tests/write-code)\n- **SubagentStop:** Marks agent completed; auto-advances phases (explore\u2192write-codebase, plan\u2192write-plan, review\u2192present-plan, etc.)\n- **TaskCreated:** Increments tasks_created counter\n- **CLI Entry:** Accepts `--hook-input` JSON argument\n\n#### **5. Auto-Commit (Async State Reader)**\n\n**Location:** `/auto_commit.py`\n\n**State Usage:**\n- Reads `DEFAULT_STATE_PATH` to extract story_id and parent_tasks for commit message context\n- Does NOT write to state\n- Uses separate `COMMIT_BATCH_PATH` ledger for batch coordination (filelock-protected)\n\n#### **6. Reminders (Read-Only Context Injection)**\n\n**Location:** `/reminder.py`\n\n**State Usage:**\n- Reads state in `get_post_tool_reminder()`, `get_agent_start_reminder()`, `get_phase_transition_reminder()`\n- Uses phase, plan_review_iteration, plan_files to generate dynamic reminders\n- Never mutates state\n\n#### **7. Guardrail (Unified Dispatcher)**\n\n**Location:** `/guardrail.py`\n\n**Environment Variable:** `GUARDRAIL_STATE_PATH` (overrides DEFAULT_STATE_PATH)\n\n**State Usage:**\n- Routes all PreToolUse, PostToolUse, SubagentStop, TaskCompleted, Stop, UserPromptSubmit events\n- Loads state to determine current phase and validation status\n- Implements `_phase_gate()` to block non-Agent tools during agent-only phases\n- Implements `_handle_exit_plan_mode_pre()` with plan template validation\n\n#### **8. Build Entry (Workflow Activation)**\n\n**Location:** `/lib/build_entry.py`\n\n**State Usage:**\n- StateStore(PATH/.../state.json) - creates global state_store instance\n- Calls `state_store.update()` to set `workflow_active=True`\n- Reads state in `_get_open_prs()` / `_get_project_tasks()` calls\n\n#### **9. Test Files**\n\n| File | State Usage |\n|------|------------|\n| `/tests/conftest.py` | Fixtures: `tmp_state_file`, `mock_state_store`, `mock_session_state` (SessionState) |\n| `/tests/test_state_store.py` | Unit tests for StateStore: load, save, update, get, set, reset, delete, archive |\n| `/tests/test_file_manager.py` | Unit tests for FileManager file locking & operations |\n\n---\n\n### **DEFAULT_STATE_PATH References**\n\n| Source File | Definition | Value |\n|------------|-----------|-------|\n| `/config/paths.py` | PRIMARY | `Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent / \"state.json\"` |\n| `/session_state.py` | OVERRIDE | `Path(__file__).resolve().parent / \"state.json\"` (when no session_id) |\n| All dispatchers | IMPORT | `Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent / \"state.json\"` (hardcoded in each dispatcher) |\n| `/guardrail.py` | ENV VAR | `GUARDRAIL_STATE_PATH` env var (fallback: DEFAULT_STATE_PATH) |\n| `/recorder.py` | ENV VAR | `RECORDER_STATE_PATH` env var (fallback: DEFAULT_STATE_PATH) |\n\n**Physical Location:** `.claude/hooks/workflow/state.json` (single global file by default)\n\n---\n\n### **State Structure (Flat Model)**\n\nThe state uses a **single flat JSON object** with keys:\n\n```\nworkflow_active (bool)\nworkflow_type (str: \"implement\" or \"plan\")\nsession_id (str)\nstory_id (str)\nphase (str: explore, plan, write-plan, review, present-plan, task-create, write-tests, write-code, validate, pr-create, ci-check, report, completed)\ntdd (bool)\nskip_explore, skip_research (bool)\ninstructions (str)\n\nagents (list[dict]): [{agent_type, status: \"running\"/\"completed\", tool_use_id}, ...]\nplan_file (str)\nplan_written (bool)\nplan_review_iteration (int)\nplan_review_scores (dict)\nplan_review_status (str)\nplan_files_cache (list[str])\ncodebase_written (bool)\n\ntest_files_created (list[str])\ntest_review_result (str)\ntest_run_executed (bool)\n\nvalidation_result (str: \"Pass\"/\"Fail\")\npr_status (str)\nci_status (str)\nci_check_executed (bool)\nreport_written (bool)\n\ntasks_created (int)\ntasks (list[dict]): [{id, subject, description, status, subtasks}, ...]\nfiles_written (list[str])\ntool_enforcement (dict)\nforce_stop (dict)\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Session vs. Global State Model**\n\n**Current Architecture:**\n- **Single DEFAULT_STATE_PATH** at `.claude/hooks/workflow/state.json` (global)\n- **SessionState class supports per-session paths** (`.claude/sessions/session_{session_id}/state.json`) but rarely used\n- Most hooks use **global state only** via hardcoded DEFAULT_STATE_PATH\n- Only `/lib/set_story_id.py` uses SessionState with per-session paths\n\n**Implication:** Only one workflow can run at a time in the global state. Per-session support exists but is not actively used.\n\n---\n\n### **File Locking Summary**\n\n| Component | Lock Type | Lock File | Scope |\n|-----------|-----------|-----------|-------|\n| StateStore | FileLock | `state.json.lock` | Per-state-file (atomic updates) |\n| auto_commit.py | FileLock | `commit_batch.json.lock` | Batch ledger coordination |\n\n**Lock Duration:** Held only during read-modify-write operations, immediately released after.\n\n---\n\n### **Summary Table: All 46 Files Using State**\n\nSee the grep output above for the complete list. Key categories:\n\n1. **Core State Classes** (2): session_state.py, state_store.py\n2. **Dispatchers** (6): session_start.py, pre_tool_use.py, post_tool_use.py, subagent_start.py, subagent_stop.py, user_prompt_submit.py\n3. **Guards** (8): write_guard.py, bash_guard.py, stop_guard.py, read_guard.py, agent_guard.py, task_guard.py, skill_guard.py, webfetch_guard.py, subagent_stop_guard.py\n4. **Core Logic** (3): recorder.py, guardrail.py, auto_commit.py\n5. **Initialization** (3): set_story_id.py, workflow_initializer.py, build_entry.py\n6. **Reminders & Logging** (2): reminder.py, logger.py\n7. **Tests** (12+): test_*.py files, conftest.py\n8. **Dry Runs** (2): plan_dry_run.py, implement_dry_run.py"}], "totalDurationMs": 81009, "totalTokens": 66252, "totalToolUseCount": 32, "usage": {"input_tokens": 6, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 111, "cache_read_input_tokens": 62738, "output_tokens": 3397, "server_tool_use": {"web_search_requests": 0, "web_fetch_requests": 0}, "service_tier": "standard", "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 111}, "inference_geo": "", "iterations": [], "speed": "standard"}}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01VHCvqroBwkRWSD4WXTh4Sr"}}
